Add a few lines of code into your README. People looking to better understand your coding style will appreciate this.

Now they don't need to dig through your code because examples are readily available. This shows recruiters you write efficient code and uphold proper coding standards.

```javascript
// Example: Fetching recipes from API
const fetchRecipes = async (ingredient) => {
  const response = await fetch(
    `${API_URL}/search?q=${ingredient}`
  );
  return response.json();
};
```
